    "factsheet": [
        {
            "heading": "The London Cancer Hub is Europe's leading Oncology District",
            "paragraphs": [
                "The partnership was formed in 2015 between The London Borough of Sutton, The Institute of Cancer Research, The Royal Marsden NHS Trust, Epsom, St Helier NHS Trust, and The GLA.",
                "The Council is embarking on major regeneration to develop what is now Europe’s leading oncology district into the global centre of innovation in cancer research, drug discovery and clinical excellence"
            ]
        },
        {
            "heading": "The major regeneration will deliver:",
            "paragraphs": [
                "c.100,000 square metres of commercial and academic space\nc.£1.2bn GVA to the UK economy annually;\nThe creation of up to 13,000 jobs \nHigh-quality placemaking\nA national solution to addressing cancer inequalities"
            ]
        },
        {
            "heading": "The LCH is currently home to the following:",
            "paragraphs": [
                "The Institute of Cancer Research - including their Centre for Cancer Drug Discovery (CCDD) which is a world-first Darwinian facility to tackle cancer’s ability to evolve resistance to treatment.",
                "The Royal Marsden Hospital - an internationally renowned as one of the leading cancer centres in the world.",
                "The Innovation Gateway - a new life science workspace, hosting a collaborative life science community of small and start-up businesses.",
                "Harris Academy at Sutton  - an award-winning science specialist secondary school that is the largest Passivhaus school in the UK.",
                "Maggie’s Cancer Centre (The Royal Marsden) -  a facility providing direct support for cancer patients from the Royal Marsden,  designed by an award winning architect and designer to create a therapeutic environment."
            ]
        }
    ],
